b'Sir Don Bradman on seeing Dhyan Chand said, \xe2\x80\x9cYou score goals like runs\xe2\x80\x9d.\nSuch a legend needs to be known and celebrated so much more.'
b'During 1936 Olympics, the whole city of Berlin had posters: \xe2\x80\x9cVisit the hockey stadium to watch the Indian magician Dhyan Chand in action.\xe2\x80\x9d'
b'It is said that in the 1936 Berlin Olympics, Dhyan Chand who was the flag-bearer,\xc2\xa0refused to salute Adolf Hitler.\xc2\xa0What a man !'
b'Barefoot, he scored 3 goals.What a legend !In Netherlands,once\nthe authorities broke his hockey stick to check if there was a magnet inside.'
b'During the1936 Olympic final against Germany, it\xe2\x80\x99s said that Dhyan Chand\xc2\xa0removed his spiked shoes\xc2\xa0& stockings in 2nd half & played barefoot'
b'He was called Chand by his team-mates because he used to wait for the moon to come out for practice. He was also called\xc2\xa0as "The Wizard"'
b'Every child in the country must know about the legend Major Dhyanchand was.He joined the Indian army at the age of 16 and retired in 1956.'
